#require "hbssl"
#require "hbtip"

#if ! defined( __HBSCRIPT__HBSHELL )
    REQUEST __HBEXTERN__HBSSL__
#endif


#ifndef _SIMPLEIO_CH
#define _SIMPLEIO_CH

#command ?  [ <xList,...> ] => ( OutStd( hb_eol() ) [, OutStd( <xList> ) ] )
#command ?? [ <xList,...> ] => OutStd( <xList> )

#command ACCEPT TO <idVar> => <idVar> := StrTran( FReadStr( hb_GetStdIn(), 256 ), hb_eol() )
#command ACCEPT <cPrompt> TO <idVar> => ? <cPrompt> ; ACCEPT TO <idVar>

#endif

function main()

    local cFrom := <mailto:'wilson.josenet@gmail.com|'wilson.josenet@gmail.com>'
    local cPassword := 'xxxxxxx'
    local cTo       := <mailto:'wilsongamboa@hotmail.com|'wilsongamboa@hotmail.com>'
    local cHost     := 'localhost'

    _Main( cFrom, cPassword, cTo, cHost )

return nil

PROCEDURE _Main( cFrom, cPassword, cTo, cHost )

   LOCAL nPort
   LOCAL lSTARTTLS := .F.

   IF ! tip_SSL()
      ? "Error: Requires SSL support"
      RETURN
   ENDIF

   hb_default( @cFrom    , "<<mailto:from@example.net|from@example.net>>" )
   hb_default( @cPassword, "password" )
   hb_default( @cTo      , "<mailto:to@example.com|to@example.com>" )
   hb_default( @cHost    , "localhost" )

   cHost := Lower( cHost )

   /* SMTPS works with SSL/TLS on port 465 and with STARTTLS
      on port 587. STARTTLS mode is fully automatic and requires
      SSL/TLS be disabled at first (it will be activated on
      request after STARTTLS command) */

   DO CASE
   CASE cHost == "apple" .OR. "@icloud.com" $ cFrom .OR. "@mac.com" $ cFrom .OR. "@me.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.mail.me.com|smtp.mail.me.com>"; lSTARTTLS := .T.
   CASE cHost == "fastmail" .OR. "@fastmail.com" $ cFrom .OR. "@fastmail.fm" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.fastmail.com|smtp.fastmail.com>"
   CASE cHost == "<http://gmx.net|gmx.net>" .OR. "@gmx.net" $ cFrom .OR. "@gmx.ch" $ cFrom .OR. "@gmx.de" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://mail.gmx.net|mail.gmx.net>"; lSTARTTLS := .T.
   CASE cHost == "google" .OR. "@gmail.com" $ cFrom .OR. "@googlemail.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.gmail.com|smtp.gmail.com>"
   CASE cHost == "<http://mail.ru|mail.ru>" .OR. "@mail.ru" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.mail.ru|smtp.mail.ru>"
   CASE cHost == "netease" .OR. "@163.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.163.com|smtp.163.com>"
   CASE cHost == "office365"
      cHost := "<http://smtp.office365.com|smtp.office365.com>"; lSTARTTLS := .T.
   CASE cHost == "outlook" .OR. "@outlook.com" $ cFrom .OR. "@hotmail.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp-mail.outlook.com|smtp-mail.outlook.com>"; lSTARTTLS := .T.
   CASE cHost == "sina" .OR. "@sina.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.vip.sina.com|smtp.vip.sina.com>"
   CASE cHost == "uol" .OR. "@uol.com.br" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtps.uol.com.br|smtps.uol.com.br>"
   CASE cHost == "yahoo" .OR. "@yahoo.com" $ cFrom
      cHost := "<http://smtp.mail.yahoo.com|smtp.mail.yahoo.com>"
   CASE ":" $ cHost
      IF TUrl():New( cHost ):nPort != -1
         nPort := TUrl():New( cHost ):nPort
      ENDIF
      lSTARTTLS := ( nPort == 587 )
      cHost := TUrl():New( cHost ):cServer
   ENDCASE

   hb_default( @nPort, iif( lSTARTTLS, 587, 465 ) )

   ? "Host:", cHost, hb_ntos( nPort ), iif( lSTARTTLS, "(STARTTLS)", "" )

   ? tip_MailSend( ;
      cHost, ;
      nPort, ;
      cFrom, ;
      cTo, ;
      NIL /* CC */, ;
      {} /* BCC */, ;
      "test: body", ;
      "test: subject", ;
      NIL /* attachment */, ;
      cFrom, ;
      cPassword, ;
      "", ;
      NIL /* nPriority */, ;
      NIL /* lRead */, ;
      .T. /* lTrace */, ;
      .F., ;
      NIL /* lNoAuth */, ;
      NIL /* nTimeOut */, ;
      NIL /* cReplyTo */, ;
      nPort == 465 )

   RETURN
